articles.title: Wrestling President Says Video Game Is Finished, But Its Devs Disagree
articles.author: Isaiah Colbert
articles.excerpt: AEW Fight Forever is available for preorder despite not having a release date
articles.summary:
The backstage drama in the world of professional wrestling can upstage the theatrics inside the squared circle. 
AEW
's lack of a release date for its upcoming video game is starting to wear thin on fans. 
AEW, short for 
All Elite Wrestling
, is a new wrestling promotion on TNT that was founded by Tony Khan, the owner of the NFL's Jacksonville Jaguars, alongside professional wrestlers and executive vice presidents Kenny Omega, Matt and Nick Jackson, and WWE superstar Cody Rhodes in 2019. AEW first announced its video game, 
AEW Fight Forever
, in the second year of the promotion's existence.

articles.title: AEW ALL IN: Wembley Stadium Pre-Sale Registrations Indicate Massive Crowd
articles.author: Liam Crowley
articles.excerpt: Five years ago, Cody Rhodes took that bet. When a prominent wrestling journalist claimed that Ring [...]
articles.summary: Five years ago, Cody Rhodes took that bet. When a prominent wrestling journalist claimed that Ring of Honor would not be able to draw 10,000 fans, Rhodes got to work alongside the Young Bucks to birth ALL IN, the largest independent wrestling show ever produced. Combined with Chris Jericho and Kenny Omega's NJPW Wrestle Kingdom match earlier that year, ALL IN inspired Tony Khan to create AEW, a still-young promotion that has skyrocketed to becoming the second-largest wrestling company in the world today.

articles.title: AEW Dynamite Preview: Keith Lee vs. Chris Jericho, Two Championship Matches, MJF Appears
articles.author: Liam Crowley
articles.excerpt: All Elite Wrestling's once distant road to AEW Double or Nothing has reached its halfway point. [...]
articles.summary: All Elite Wrestling's once distant road to AEW Double or Nothing has reached its halfway point. With fallout from AEW Revolution mostly in the rear view but the company's next pay-per-view still six weeks away, AEW has put an emphasis on televised feuds that could very well be resolved well before AEW Double or Nothing but also have the potential to extend to the Las Vegas-based event. One rivalry that began brewing last week comes in the form of Chris Jericho vs. Keith Lee. The Limitless One confronted The Ocho in a backstage segment which set up an in-ring clash between the two that will go down tonight.

articles.title: CM Punk's Potential Return To AEW Raises Plenty Of Questions
articles.author: Colin Tessier
articles.excerpt: Should CM Punk return to All Elite Wrestling? Perhaps literally, that is the million-dollar question. Rumors and speculation continue to swirl about the former AEW World Champion, and the buzz has…
articles.summary:
Should CM Punk return to All Elite Wrestling?
Perhaps literally, that is the million-dollar question. Rumors and speculation continue to swirl about the former AEW World Champion, and the buzz has reached a fever pitch following a new report from Fightful Select, which stated that CM Punk has repeatedly expressed his interest in a comeback to AEW. On top of that, AEW star Dax Harwood recently noted that Punk misses wrestling, and he wants to give back to the fans.
With the news that AEW will make its debut in the United Kingdom at Wembley Stadium in August, it's easy to connect the dots and predict that CM Punk will return to the fold in time for the major show.

FTR have revealed how long their new AEW contracts are.
 
Dax Harwood and Cash Wheeler, collectively known as FTR, signed with AEW in May 2020. They were coming off a successful WWE run in which they became the first WWE Tag Team Triple Crown Winners. Since they joined AEW, the duo have won the AEW, ROH, AAA, and IWGP tag team titles. Their contracts were coming up on April 2023, and they took some time off to make a decision.

articles.title: Top AEW Star Currently Injured, Pulled From Upcoming NJPW Appearance
articles.author: Liam Crowley
articles.excerpt: The injury bug continues to plague All Elite Wrestling. Top star Eddie Kingston is currently on [...]
articles.summary: The injury bug continues to plague All Elite Wrestling. Top star Eddie Kingston is currently on the shelf with an undisclosed injury, forcing him to be pulled from his scheduled appearance at this weekend's NJPW Collision. Kingston's last contest came two weeks ago at ROH Supercard of Honor, Ring of Honor's WWE WrestleMania 39 weekend show. At that event, Kingston challenged ROH World Champion Claudio Castagnoli, ultimately falling short to his long-time rival. That recent challenge came in the midst of a storyline between Kingston, AEW and ROH, as Kingston "quit" AEW before showing up on ROH TV earlier this year.

articles.summary:
AEW Fight Forever, the officially licensed All Elite Wrestling game developed by Yuke's and published by THQ Nordic, is supposed to be out this year. But a series of comments from AEW leadership and the game's developers have left fans confused as to the game's actual development status.
The confusion can be traced back to February when AEW wrestler and executive vice president Kenny Omega said on the 
Swerve City Podcast
 (via 
WrestleZone
) that "the game has been done," but was currently in limbo trying to get an ESRB rating finalized.

articles.title: Backstage News on Santana's AEW Contract Status Amid Hiatus
articles.author: Marc Middleton
articles.excerpt: Santana remains signed to AEW. Santana has not wrestled since the Blood & Guts match that saw The Blackpool Combat Club, Ortiz and Santana defeat The
articles.summary:
Santana remains signed to AEW.


Santana has not wrestled since the Blood & Guts match that saw The Blackpool Combat Club, Ortiz and Santana defeat The Jericho Appreciation Society on the June 29, 2022 edition of AEW Dynamite. He suffered a torn ACL in that match, but had already been teaming less with longtime partner Ortiz as they had a private falling out. Before the injury, Santana was publicly counting down what many assumed to be the expiration of his AEW contract.


In an update, a new report from Fightful Select confirms that Santana is still signed to a contract with AEW, and he has been paid through the duration of his injury.

articles.summary:
Tony Khan is making headlines again as AEW introduced indie star Daisy K to their roster through his debut on Dark.

In his debut match, Daisy K fought against Josh Woods in a hard-fought battle. While Woods ultimately came out on top with a knee strike and a suplex into the bottom turnbuckle, K showed great potential and proved that he belongs in the ring with the best of them.

Before joining AEW, Daisy K had already made a name for himself on the independent circuit, holding the SPCW Championship.

articles.title: Backstage Update on Santana's Current AEW Status, Is He Still Under Contract?
articles.excerpt: A new backstage report has an update on the current contract status of Santana and AEW after he was injured during Blood & Guts last year.
articles.summary:
– 
Fightful Select
 has an update on MIA AEW talent Santana, who hasn't appeared in AEW since the Blood & Guts match that took place on the June 29, 2022 edition of AEW Dynamite. According to Fightful's report, Santana is still with the company at the moment.


Santana reportedly had a falling out with his longtime tag team partner Ortiz and was already teaming with him on a less frequent basis when he suffered an ACL injury in the Blood & Guts match. Before that, Fightful Select notes that Santana had been counting down until his AEW contract expired.

articles.summary: CM Punk is looking to come back to AEW, according to the latest Fightful Select report from Sean Ross Sapp. Punk's issues with AEW are well-documented — the scathing comments he made in the post-show press conference after the All Out pay-per-view and subsequent locker room brawl with Kenny Omega and The Young Bucks resulted in him getting stripped of the AEW World Championship and effectively scrubbed from AEW programming, and he's still been recovering from a torn triceps he suffered in his most recent match.

articles.title: 10 Former WWE Wrestlers Who Have Failed In AEW
articles.author: AEW
articles.excerpt: These former WWE wrestlers couldn't find their footing in AEW and struggled to find success.
articles.summary:
Since AEW began back in 2019, they have welcomed into the roster many wrestlers who formerly worked for WWE. There was some criticism for this but it is hard to blame Tony Khan for wanting to bring in the best possible free agents, and many of those arrived on the back of WWE releases.

Not all of these signings have been a success unfortunately, and have ultimately been failures for AEW. The level of 'failure' for each of these wrestlers is different based on their standings in the company, and the reason for a lack of success can come down to various factors.

articles.summary: Brian Cage is sticking with AEW and Ring of Honor, according to Fightful Select 's Sean Ross Sapp. Cage is currently one-third of the ROH Six-Man Tag Team Champions but had his deal expire following the Supercard of Honor pay-per-view earlier this month. While there was interest from top talent within WWE and Cage had openly discussed his frustration with his booking in the past, he preferred the new offer AEW provided for him. Last week's AEW Rampage saw Cage (and by extension, The Embassy faction) align with Swerve Strickland as he delivered a vicious attack on Darby Allin.

AEW Dynamite: AEW डायनामाइट (Dynamite) का आखिरी एपिसोड बेहतरीन रहा था। इस शो को कई सारे फैंस ने खूब पसंद किया था। अब AEW के इस टीवी शो की व्यूअरशिप का खुलासा देखने को मिल गया है। दरअसल, इस शो की रेटिंग्स एक मिलियन से बहुत कम रही और पिछले हफ्ते के मुकाबले कंपनी को नुकसान हुआ है। पूर्व WWE सुपरस्टार जैफ हार्डी (Jeff Hardy) की वापसी हुई थी और इसके बावजूद भी कंपनी को फायदा नहीं हुआ।

WrestleNomics के ब्रेंडन थर्स्टन ने हाल ही में AEW Dynamite के 12 अप्रैल 2023 के एपिसोड की औसतन रेटिंग्स बताई है। इस शो को 8 लाख 66 हजार लोगों ने देखा है। इस हफ्ते सभी को उम्मीद थी कि व्यूअरशिप में बढ़ोतरी होगी लेकिन ऐसा कुछ नहीं हुआ। पिछले हफ्ते के मुकाबले और गिरावट आ गई। आपको बता दें कि पिछले हफ्ते इस शो को 877,000 लोगों ने देखा है।

AEW के फ्लैगशिप शो की इस हफ्ते की 18-49 की डेमो रेटिंग्स भी बहुत कम रही। दरअसल, Dynamite को 0.

articles.title: Jeff Hardy Returns to AEW on This Week's AEW Dynamite
articles.author: Connor Casey
articles.excerpt: Jeff Hardy officially returned to AEW Dynamite this week, saving his brother Matt Hardy, Isiah [...]
articles.summary:
Jeff Hardy officially returned to AEW Dynamite this week, saving his brother Matt Hardy, Isiah Kassidy and Hook in a brawl with The Firm. "The Charismatic Enigma" evened the odds in the fight, which ended with him hitting a Swanton Bomb. This marked the first time Hardy has been back on TV since his June 2022 arrest.

After a controversial departure from WWE in late 2021, Jeff arrived in AEW in March 2022. He and Matt Hardy immediately reunited to begin a Hardy Boyz tag team tour to prove they're the greatest tag team in all of space and time.

articles.title: Dax Harwood Talks Up CM Punk AEW Comeback
articles.author: Andy H Murray
articles.excerpt: "I talk to punk almost every day and Punk misses wrestling, that's your headline."
articles.summary:
AEW
FTR's Dax Harwood continues to talk up the possibility of CM Punk returning to AEW, doing so again on this week's episode of his 
FTR with Dax podcast
.
Harwood - who had previously pitched FTR and Punk vs. The Elite as a potential match at AEW's upcoming Wembley Stadium supershow, All In - unpacked his fantasy booking. Calling Punk "the biggest name in AEW", he noted that if the goal is to take Tony Khan's promotion to the next level, it makes sense to use one of the biggest wrestlers on the planet to make money.

articles.summary:
CM Punk's AEW return was thought to be impossible after the latest 'deleted Instagram story' saga. The former world champion targeted fellow stars Jon Moxley, Chris Jericho, and even AEW President Tony Khan for being unprofessional. Reconciliation seemed out of the question, but recent events state otherwise.

The 44-year-old megastar was written off television due to multiple injury-related issues following All Out 2022. His controversial statements on the post-match media scrum also proved detrimental to his career.

During the April 14 episode of AEW Rampage, the broadcast team announced that White will face Komander on the April 19 episode of AEW Dynamite. The match will mark the first time White competes as a contracted member of the AEW roster. White appeared on the April 5 episode of AEW Dynamite, and Tony Khan subsequently announced that he signed with the company. White competed on AEW Rampage and at AEW x NJPW Forbidden Door 2022, but he has yet to wrestle on AEW Dynamite.

articles.title: Chris Jericho Calls Out AEW: All In London Critics
articles.author: Matthew Aguilar
articles.excerpt: AEW is embarking on its biggest event to date at Wembley Stadium later this year, and it's driven [...]
articles.summary: AEW is embarking on its biggest event to date at Wembley Stadium later this year, and it's driven up a conversation regarding what will be looked at as a success. The event is AEW: All In London, and with a capacity of 90,000, will be the largest event AEW has ever run. AEW's attendance record is currently at 20,177, which was Dynamite Grand Slam at Arthur Ashe Stadium, so even if the stadium is half full, it will soar past that total. There have been some detractors since the announcement, and Chris Jericho had a message for all those who are being critical of the move and proclaimed the event a failure before it has even happened.

articles.title: Billie Starkz Reportedly Signed by AEW
articles.excerpt: According to AEW broadcaster Tony Schiavone, AEW has signed 18-year-old indie wrestling sensation Billie Starkz to an AEW contract.
articles.summary:
– During the latest edition of his 
What Happened When podcast
 (via 
WrestlingInc.com
), AEW broadcaster Tony Schiavone stated that 18-year-old wrestler Billie Starkz has signed with AEW.


Starkz recently competed at AEW Battle of the Belts over the weekend, challenging TBS Champion Jade Cargill in a losing effort for the TBS Title. She's also competed on multiple editions of AEW Dark earlier this year.


Earlier this year
, Starkz said she was enjoying her free agency and her immediate plan was to finish high school, as she's slated to graduate in May.

articles.title: Dax Harwood: FTR And CM Punk vs. The Elite; If You Want To Sell 50K Tickets, That's The Dream Match
articles.author: Sean Ross Sp
articles.excerpt: FTR is excited for Wembley Stadium.
articles.summary:
AEW will head to Wembley Stadium on August 27 for their biggest event ever All In. 
 
Wembley Stadium holds roughly 90,000 fans, and though it is unknown how many seats will be available following event configuration, AEW will be looking to break records with the attendance number. This will mark the first wrestling event at the modern Wembley Stadium. WWE packed an announced 80,355 fans into the old Wembley Stadium for SummerSlam 1992. 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
Related Article
 
Orange Cassidy To Compete At NJPW Collision In Philadelphia, Capital Collision Card Announced
 
 


 
Speaking to 
Raj Prashad of Uproxx
, FTR has a dream match in mind to bring the fans in and take AEW to the next level.

articles.title: "He chose AEW"
articles.author: Sam Palmer
articles.excerpt: Former AEW World Champion Chris Jericho has recently gone on record in saying that one of All Elite Wrestling's most recent signings is a statement of intent.
articles.summary:
Former AEW World Champion Chris Jericho has recently gone on record in saying that one of All Elite Wrestling's most recent signings is a statement of intent.

The signing in question is former IWGP Heavyweight Champion Jay White, who made his shocking debut on the April 5th edition of Dynamite by attacking Ricky Starks and aligning with Juice Robinson.

Many fans thought that "Switchblade" would be signing with WWE after his departure from NJPW in February. Instead, he decided to become an "All Elite" and signed a multi-year deal with Tony Khan's company.

articles.summary:
AEW Rampage is set to air on a different day on April 22.
 
The 
schedule on TNT's website

articles.summary:
Will Ospreay comments on the news that AEW is coming to Wembley Stadium.
During the April 5 episode of AEW Dynamite, All Elite Wrestling announced that their United Kingdom debut will be held at Wembley Stadium on August 27. Titled AEW All In at Wembley Stadium, the event has AEW fans buzzing and wrestlers expressing their interest in being a part of it.
Ospreay, who worked with AEW multiple times in 2022, including the AEW x NJPW Forbidden Door pay-per-view, was asked about his interest in All In when speaking with Dark Puroresu Flowsion.

articles.title: AEW Star Expresses Interest in WWE Run
articles.author: Liam Crowley
articles.excerpt: While professional wrestling has evolved into a giant multiverse of sorts, with most wrestlers [...]
articles.summary: While professional wrestling has evolved into a giant multiverse of sorts, with most wrestlers popping up in a plethora of promotions throughout their careers, the through line between WWE and AEW has largely been a one-way street. Upon the company's inception in 2019, AEW stood on the shoulders of former WWE talent like Cody Rhodes, Chris Jericho and Jon Moxley. Over the next three years, AEW would add dozens of formerly WWE talent, bolstering its roster with past WWE Champions like CM Punk and WrestleMania main-eventers of yesteryear such as Bryan Danielson.

articles.title: CM Punk 'Wants to Come Back' to AEW
articles.author: Jason Hall
articles.excerpt: Former All Elite Wrestling World Heavyweight Champion CM Punk reportedly "misses wrestling" and "wants to come back" to AEW, according to friend and colleague Dax Harwood of the AEW Tag-Team champions FTR.
articles.summary:
Former All Elite Wrestling World Heavyweight Champion CM Punk reportedly "misses wrestling" and "wants to come back" to AEW, according to friend and colleague Dax Harwood of the AEW Tag-Team champions FTR.

"I talk to Punk almost every day, and Punk misses wrestling, that's your headline, Punk misses wrestling, and Punk wants to come back. And he wants to give back to the fans, he wants to get back to wrestling. So I'll leave it at that," Harwood said during the latest episode of his FTR with Dax Harwood podcast.

articles.title: FTR Reveal Length of New AEW Contracts and Retirement Plans
articles.author: Liam Crowley
articles.excerpt: FTR are staying in All Elite Wrestling. Dax Harwood and Cash Wheeler's most successful year of [...]
articles.summary: FTR are staying in All Elite Wrestling. Dax Harwood and Cash Wheeler's most successful year of their careers concluded with a whimper, as the tag team lost three sets of championships within a matter of weeks. After being defeated by The Gunns on an episode of AEW Dynamite in December 2022, Harwood and Wheeler took a sabbatical from the company, noting that they would be taking time off to decide their next career steps. They returned at March's AEW Revolution, seeking vengeance on The Gunns, who were now AEW Tag Team Champions.
